  <h3>THIS CONTRACT CONTAINS A BINDING ARBITRATION PROVISION (INCLUDING A CLASS ACTION WAIVER) WHICH MAY BE ENFORCED BY THE PARTIES. </h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
       <strong><u>1. General Description of Services.</u></strong>
       SeatUs Technologies LLC dba Wyth (“<strong>Wyth</strong>”) offers a carpool ride-matching platform geared toward providing a platform for college students, graduate students, faculty and staff with an active “.edu” email account who own vehicles and are looking to drive a carpool (each, a “<strong>Driver Member</strong>”) and college students, graduate students, faculty and staff with an active “.edu” email account who are looking for carpool rides (each, a “<strong>Rider Member</strong>”) to offer and search for carpool rides (the “<strong>Services</strong>”). 
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong><u>2. General Purpose of Agreement.</u></strong>
        This Wyth Membership Agreement – Driver Member (the “<strong>Agreement</strong>”) governs the relationship between and establishes the rights and responsibilities of, Wyth and you (<strong>“you</strong>” or “<strong>your</strong>”) as a Driver Member of the Services.  In this Agreement, you and Wyth may be referred to together as the “Parties” and individually as a “Party,” and Driver Members and Rider Members may be referred to together herein as “Users.” The terms of the FAQs (available at <a href="https://protect-us.mimecast.com/s/s90tCxk7GYCOo24WU8aVPM">https://gowyth.com/faq/</a>) (the “<strong>FAQs</strong>”), which are also available on the Wyth mobile application (the “<strong>App</strong>”) and the Wyth website (available at www.gowyth.com) (the “<strong>Website</strong>,” and together with the App, the “<strong>Platform</strong>”), are incorporated into this Agreement by reference, as in effect from time to time.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong><u>3. Content Representations; Rider Member Eligibility.</u></strong> <br>
        <ul>
            <li><strong><u>3.1 Your Representations and Warranties Regarding All Content You Provide to Wyth or Others in Connection with the Services</strong></u>. You represent and warrant that any and all information, data, text, photographs, graphics, messages or other materials (collectively, “<strong>Content</strong>”) that is publically or privately posted, transmitted, provided or made available (in any manner whatsoever) (collectively, Content that is “<strong>Supplied</strong>,” that you “<strong>Supply</strong>,” or that one “<strong>Supplies</strong>”) by you to Wyth or to others in connection with the Services is true, accurate, current and complete. If, while you are a User of the Services, any Content which you Supply or have Supplied to Wyth or others in connection with the Services becomes inaccurate or incomplete at any time, you agree that you will promptly notify Wyth and any others with whom you have Supplied such Content. If you Supply any Content to Wyth or to others in connection with the Services that (as determined in Wyth’s sole discretion) is untrue, inaccurate, incomplete, fraudulent, or misleading, Wyth reserves the right to immediately terminate this Agreement and your access to the Services.</li>
            <li><strong><u>3.2 Driver Member Eligibility</u></strong>
                <ul>
                    <li style="list-style: none">(a) To be eligible to use the Services as a Driver Member, you must meet the following criteria (the “<strong>Driver Member Criteria</strong>”):
                        <ul class="listStyleNone">
                            <li>(1) Be at least 18 years of age;</li>
                            <li>(2) Possess a valid U.S. driver’s license;</li>
                            <li>(3) Have a “.edu” email address;</li>
                            <li>(4) Have lawful possession of an Eligible Vehicle (as defined below); </li>
                            <li>(5) Have had no felony convictions or convictions for offenses that involve alcohol, drugs, or violence, or that are sexual-in-nature; and </li>
                            <li>(6) Have signed and entered into this Agreement.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>(b) Prior to accessing the Services as a Driver Member, you must have completed the Driver Member registration process via the Platform.  The Driver Member registration process includes Supplying Content in response to the Driver Member profile questions; the Platform uses such Content to create a User profile (a “Profile”) for you. You represent and warrant that if you are accessing the Services as a Driver Member that you meet and will continue to meet the Driver Member Criteria during the Term of this Agreement (as provided in Section 13) and that you will report any change in your compliance with the Driver Member Criteria to Wyth as soon as practicable, but no more than 24 hours after such change.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong><u>3.3 Eligible Vehicles.</u></strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>(a) An “<strong>Eligible Vehicle</strong>” is a personal passenger (non-commercial) vehicle:
                        <ul>
                            <li>(1) of which you have lawful possession;</li>
                            <li>(2) for which you have all required permissions to use in connection with the Services and any Carpool Trip;</li>
                            <li>(3) which is registered and insured as required by applicable Law, including in at least the minimum financial responsibility amounts of the state in which such vehicle is registered (collectively, the “<strong>Required Insurance</strong>”);</li>
                            <li>(4) which is designed to transport no more than 8 persons (including the driver);</li>
                            <li>(5) which has a gross vehicle weight of less than 10,000 pounds;</li>
                            <li>(6) for which use of the vehicle in connection with the Services and any Carpool Trip will not violate the terms of the Required Insurance;</li>
                            <li>(7) which is in good working condition with fully-functional seatbelts;</li>
                            <li>(8) which is not connected to any trailer or similar towed object;</li>
                            <li>(9) which is roadworthy (including having no check-engine lights lit); </li>
                            <li>(10)    which is not licensed as a transportation network company or other “for-hire” or commercial vehicle; and</li>
                            <li>(11) which is up to date with all vehicle maintenance and upkeep recommended by the vehicle’s owners’ manual, maintenance guide, or similar document;</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong><u>4. Offering a Carpool Trip.</u></strong>
        <ul>
            <li><strong><u>4.1 Carpool Trip Definitions.</u></strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>“<strong>Arrival Time</strong>” means the anticipated time that the Eligible Vehicle will arrive at a Destination for a Carpool Trip as indicated by the Platform;</li>
                    <li>(b) “<strong>Available Seat</strong>” means a passenger seat with a fully functioning seatbelt in an Eligible Vehicle which a Driver Member would like to make available for Rider Members to bid on with respect to a Carpool Trip; </li>
                    <li>“<strong>Carpool Trip</strong>” means an upcoming trip a Driver Member plans to take using an Eligible Vehicle and that such Driver Member would like to make available for carpooling by allowing Rider Members to bid on at least one Available Seat;</li>
                    <li>(d) “<strong>Departure Time</strong>” means the time that a Carpool Trip will begin as indicated by the Platform;</li>
                    <li>(e)  “<strong>Origin</strong>” means the starting location of a Carpool Trip as indicated by the Platform; and</li>
                    <li>(f) “<strong>Destination</strong>” means the ending destination of a Carpool Trip as indicated by the Platform.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong><u>4.2 Offering a Carpool Trip.</u></strong> If you are a Driver Member, you can use the Platform in order to offer Rider Members the opportunity to search for and bid on Available Seats for a Carpool Trip that you plan to take. In order to do so, you will use the Platform to Supply certain information about the type of Carpool Trip on which you are offering Available Seats for Rider Members to bid on including the Origin, Destination, number of Available Seats, and Departure Time with respect to such Carpool Trip. After you Supply such information, the Platform will take such information and “match” such Carpool Trip with Rider Members who may be interested in the opportunity to bid on an Available Seat for such Carpool Trip (each, a “<strong>Potential Rider</strong>,” and collectively, the “Potential Riders”). In order to Supply information about a Carpool Trip on the Platform, such Carpool Trip must have at least one Available Seat.</li>
            <li><strong><u>4.3  Matching Results.</u></strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><u>(a)  Your Receipt of Content Supplied by Potential Riders.</u></strong> . If Wyth identifies a Potential Rider for a Carpool Trip for which you have offered Available Seats, Wyth will provide you with certain Content Supplied by the Potential Rider. This Content will include the Potential Rider’s Profile, which among other things, contains information such as the Rider’s name, profile picture, cumulative star rating and number of cancelled trips.</li>
                    <li><strong><u>(b) Sharing of Content from Your Profile.</u></strong> You understand that not only will you potentially receive Content Supplied by Potential Riders (including some of their profile Content), but that Content you Supply to Wyth (including some of the Content you Supply for your Profile) may also be made available to Rider Members looking for Available Seats on which they would like to bid. Additionally, you may be contacted directly by Rider Members via the messaging and chat features in the App. With respect to Content you Supply to Wyth, you grant Wyth, its affiliates, licensees, successors, and representatives an irrevocable, perpetual, non-exclusive, fully paid-up, worldwide right and license to use, distribute, reproduce, modify, adapt, publicly perform and publicly display such Content and the irrevocable right to sublicense the Content with the sublicensee having the right to transfer or sublicense the Content with the transferor or sublicensee, respectively, having the right to use, distribute, reproduce, modify, adapt, publish, translate, publicly perform, publicly display, and prepare derivative works of, such Content (in whole or in part and including any such derivative works) and to incorporate such Content into other works in any format or medium now known or later developed. This Section 4.3(b) will survive termination of this Agreement.</li>
                    <li><strong><u>(c) No Obligation or Guarantee Regarding Number of Potential Riders. </u></strong> While it is Wyth’s desire that you find Potential Riders to fill all of the Available Seats on a Carpool Trip you are offering, Wyth does not guarantee that you will find any Potential Riders through your use of the Services, and Wyth does not guarantee that it will present you with any, or any specific number of, Potential Riders. Wyth also disclaims any obligation to continually or periodically update or rematch the Content you Supply in connection with searching for Potential Riders with any newly-available Potential Riders.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong><u>5. Accepting a Bid.</u></strong>
        <ul>
            <li><strong><u>5.1  Notification of a Bid on an Available Seat. </u></strong> If you have offered Available Seats on a Carpool Trip via the Platform, you will receive notification from the Platform if a Rider Member offers a Bid for an Available Seat for such Carpool Trip. A “<strong>Bid</strong>” is the amount of reimbursement per mile a Rider Member is offering in exchange for an Available Seat on a Carpool Trip. You are not required to accept a Bid in relation to a Carpool Trip. If you consider a Bid to be too low, you can make a counter-offer. BY ACCEPTING A BID, YOU REPRESENT THAT YOU ACKNOWLEDGE AND AGREE THAT WYTH DOES NOT CONDUCT BACKGROUND CHECKS, CREDIT CHECKS OR SIMILAR “SCREENING” ON RIDER MEMBERS OR DRIVER MEMBERS, AND THAT WYTH DOES NOT HAVE ANY OBLIGATION TO FACT-CHECK RIDER MEMBER OR DRIVER MEMBER CONTENT, SUCH AS RIDER MEMBER OR DRIVER MEMBER PROFILES, OR VERIFY THAT THE PICTURE UPLOADED TO THE RIDER MEMBER OR DRIVER MEMBER PROFILE MATCHES THE DRIVER MEMBER OR RIDER MEMBER. IT IS YOUR SOLE RESPONSIBILITY TO DETERMINE WHETHER YOU FEEL COMFORTABLE AND SAFE TAKING A CARPOOL TRIP, AND YOUR SAFETY IN CONNECTION WITH THE SERVICES AND ANY CARPOOL TRIP IS SOLELY YOUR RESPONSIBILITY.</li>
            <li><strong><u>5.2  Notification of Accepted Bid. </u></strong> If you accept a Bid for an Available Seat on a Carpool Trip, the Platform will notify the Rider Member who offered such Bid that the Bid has been accepted, and such Carpool Trip will be considered a “<strong>Confirmed Trip.</strong>” The Bid you accepted for such Available Seat for such Carpool Trip will be referred to as a “<strong>Confirmed Bid.</strong>” For the avoidance of doubt, a “<strong>Confirmed Trip</strong>” is a Carpool Trip that has at least one confirmed Rider Member passenger (due to such Rider Member having a Confirmed Bid) and that is scheduled to operate. </li>
            <li><strong><u>5.3  Significance of a Confirmed Trip. </u></strong> If a Carpool Trip you have offered via the Platform becomes a Confirmed Trip, such Carpool Trip is scheduled to operate and at least one Rider Member is relying on such Carpool Trip operating as scheduled.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong><u>6. Confirmed Trips. </u></strong>
        <ul>
            <li><strong><u>6.2  Driver Member Rules for Confirmed Trips</u></strong>
                <ul>
                    <li>(a) You will communicate to any Rider Members who have Confirmed Bids on a Confirmed Trip any reasonable vehicle rules you have for riding in your Eligible Vehicle (including no eating or drinking (except for water) or keeping voices at a reasonable volume);</li>
                    <li>(b) You will not attempt to impose illegal or unreasonable rules for riding in your Eligible Vehicle (including no water or complete silence);</li>
                    <li>(c) You will <strong>not</strong> operate a vehicle to carry out a Carpool Trip or, for avoidance of doubt, in any way connected to the Services:
                        <ul>
                            <li>(1) that is not an Eligible Vehicle; </li>
                            <li>(2) in violation of, or to violate, any law, regulation, ordinance, rule, or similar authority (each, a “Law”); </li>
                            <li>(3) unsafely or unreasonably;</li>
                            <li>(4) in a way that purposely or unreasonably deviates from an efficient route between the Origin and the Destination for such Carpool Trip;</li>
                            <li>(5) if you are under the influence of drugs, alcohol, or medication which may affect your ability to drive;</li>
                            <li>(6) without making a reasonable effort to ensure that all occupants of the vehicle including yourself are wearing their seatbelts and ensuring compliance with all applicable seatbelt laws; </li>
                            <li>(7) for transporting any property deemed hazardous by reason of being flammable, explosive, fissionable or corrosive or any drugs or contraband material; </li>
                            <li>(8) loaded beyond the manufacturer’s stated passenger capacity for such vehicle;</li>
                            <li>(9) for carrying passengers other than in the interior of the vehicle; </li>
                            <li>(10)    for carrying more passengers than there are seatbelts in the vehicle; </li>
                            <li>(11)    while operating devices that require one or both hands while driving, including, but not limited to, cell phones, mobile computers or devices that allow texting or without following any applicable local laws and regulations relating to mobile phone use; </li>
                            <li>(12)    while wearing any device that limits your ability to hear, see, or otherwise judge driving conditions; and</li>
                            <li>(13)    without following all applicable laws governing headphone use in vehicles.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong><u>6.3  During the Course of a Confirmed Trip. </u></strong> Wyth does not monitor or oversee Confirmed Trips. It is up to you to make sure that if at any time you feel unsafe on a Confirmed Trip, including if you observe a Rider Member violating the Law, that you contact the proper authorities to help.</li>
            <li><strong><u>6.4  Cancellation. </u></strong> You can cancel a Confirmed Trip at any time prior to picking up the Rider. However, your Driver Profile will reflect the number of trips cancelled and your ratings may suffer as a result of cancellations. If you cancel the Confirmed Trip, the Rider Member will be notified via email or SMS. Similarly, if the Rider Member cancels the trip, you will be notified via email or SMS, and the Rider Member will have an opportunity to bid on Available Seats again. </li>
            <li><strong><u>6.5  Reporting Violations of the “Wyth Membership Agreement -- Rider Member.”</u></strong> If you observe a Rider Member violating the “Wyth Membership Agreement -- Rider Member” [Link] (the “<strong>Rider Membership Agreement</strong>”), and if you feel it is safe to do so, you should ask such Rider Member to cease such violation, and you should promptly report such violation to local authorities (if appropriate), and to Wyth, so Wyth can investigate such violation if (in Wyth’s sole discretion) it is appropriate to do so.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong><u>7. Prohibited Uses of the Services; Wyth’s Right to Investigate and Remove Prohibited Content; Items the Services Do Not Provide. </u></strong>
        <ul>
            <li><strong><u>7.1  Prohibited Uses. </u></strong> You agree and represent that you are accessing the Services with the intent of offering carpooling opportunities and that you will not use (or attempt to use) the Services (either by your action or your omission), or take (or attempt to take) any action in connection with the Services, as follows:
                <ul>
                    <li>(a) for the purpose of obtaining personal information of a Rider Member or Driver Member;</li>
                    <li>(b) for the purpose of soliciting, selling or offering services, merchandise, or products;</li>
                    <li>(c) to find a Potential Rider using the Services and then completing payment for a trip with such Potential Rider outside of the context of the Services and the Platform;</li>
                    <li>(d) in violation of Law; </li>
                    <li>(e) to commit fraud; </li>
                    <li>(f) in connection with any for-hire, for-profit, or commercial use (including for use in connection with a transportation network company trip or food/package delivery trip);</li>
                    <li>(g) to reproduce, duplicate, copy, sell, rent, license, resell, create derivative works from, or exploit for any commercial purposes, any of the Content or Services; or</li>
                    <li>(h) to Supply Content that:
                        <ul>
                            <li>(1) is unlawful, harmful, hateful, threatening, abusive, violent, profane, discriminatory, prejudicial, disparaging, fraudulent, inaccurate, misleading, dangerous, sexual in nature, offensive, indecent, harassing, threatening, intimidating, tortious, defamatory, vulgar, obscene, libelous, invasive of another’s privacy, or otherwise objectionable; </li>
                            <li>(2) infringes any patent, trademark, trade secret, copyright or other proprietary rights (“<strong>Rights</strong>”) of any party; </li>
                            <li>(3) includes or constitutes unsolicited or unauthorized advertising, promotional material, “junk mail,” “spam,” “chain letters,” “pyramid schemes,” “spimming,” “phishing,” “trolling,” or similar activities, or</li>
                            <li>(4) contains software viruses or any other computer code, files or programs designed to interrupt, destroy or limit the functionality of any computer software or hardware or telecommunications equipment including, but not limited, to any viruses, spiders, data mines, time bombs, Trojan horses, cancelbots, or worms.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong><u>7.2  Wyth’s Right to Investigate and Remove Prohibited Content. </u></strong> Although Wyth does not approve and/or pre-screen Content, Wyth (and its employees and representatives) has the right (but not the obligation) in its sole discretion to investigate, refuse, move, or remove any Content Supplied by you for any reason Wyth (as determined in its sole discretion) deems reasonable. This Section 7.2 will survive termination of this Agreement.</li>
            <li><strong><u>7.3  Items the Services Do NOT Include. </u></strong> The Services are designed to assist Driver Members and Rider Members with offering and locating carpooling opportunities. Among other items, the Services do NOT include:
                <ul>
                    <li>(a) Providing legal advice of any kind (including advice regarding insurance requirements or taxes);</li>
                    <li>(b) Intervening in, or resolving, disputes between Users;</li>
                    <li>(c) Ensuring your safety in any interaction with a Rider Member or Driver Member or in any vehicle;</li>
                    <li>(d) Conducting background and/or credit checks on Rider Members or Driver Members or “screening” Rider Members or Driver Members or their Content for accuracy; and</li>
                    <li>(e) Ensuring you comply with, or apprising you of, any Law.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong><u>8. Fees, Charges and Payments.</u></strong>
        <ul>
            <li><strong><u>8.1  Fee for Use of Services; Method of Payment for Fee for Use of Services. </u></strong> Contemporaneously with your receipt of a notice of a Confirmed Trip, you will pay a transaction fee to Wyth plus any applicable sales and use taxes. Subject to applicable Law, by entering into this Agreement, you authorize Wyth to charge all amounts due under this Agreement to the credit card or debit card in your name you provided to Wyth (the “<strong>Payment Method</strong>”).  You are responsible for any credit card or debit card declination fees. Prepaid cards may not be used for payment. This provision will survive termination of this Agreement.</li>
            <li><strong><u>8.2  Carpool Reimbursement for a Confirmed Trip. </u></strong> Within approximately 5 days after the date of the conclusion of a Confirmed Trip, Wyth will remit to you, as reimbursement for the expenses you incurred in connection with driving such Confirmed Trip with your Eligible Vehicle, 75% of the Trip Cost paid by each Rider Member who had a Confirmed Bid on such Confirmed Trip (collectively, as to each Confirmed Trip, the “<strong>Reimbursement Amount</strong>”).
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><u>(a)  Trip Cost Definition. </u></strong> As to each Rider Member who has a Confirmed Bid in connection with a Confirmed Trip, the “<strong>Trip Cost</strong>” for such Confirmed Trip is the amount that was mutually agreed upon by the Rider Member and Driver Member.  </li>
                    <li><strong><u>(b)  Expedited Reimbursement. </u></strong> . If you would like to receive a Reimbursement Amount earlier than within 5 days, you can select this type of payout in the trip criteria. If you select Expedited Reimbursement, you will pay an expediting fee in an amount equal to 5% of the Trip Cost to Wyth plus any applicable sales and use taxes (as further described in the FAQs).</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong><u>8.3  Responsibility for Remitting Amounts Owed to Taxing Authorities. </u></strong> You are solely responsible for being aware of, and remitting, any amounts owed to taxing authorities based on any Reimbursement Amount you receive from Wyth. </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong><u>9.   Financial Responsibility for Loss; Reporting Incidents; Cooperation.</u></strong>
        <ul>
            <li><strong><u>9.1  Financial Responsibility. </u></strong>To the extent permitted by applicable Law, you are responsible for all damages, losses, costs or expenses, including attorneys’ fees, incurred by you or caused by you in connection with the Services.</li>
            <li><strong><u>9.2  Reporting of Accidents. </u></strong> Promptly on the occurrence of any incident involving vehicle damage, theft, or bodily injury (including a motor vehicle accident) in connection with a Carpool Trip, you will report such incident to Wyth and to the local law enforcement agency as applicable. Within 3 days of such incident (or earlier, if required by Law), you will file with such local law enforcement agency a written report of such incident including a written description of the incident and the insurance information of the other parties involved, if applicable. You will promptly provide a copy of such report to Wyth. You will make a reasonable effort to obtain evidence from any witnesses to the incident, if applicable. </li>
            <li><strong><u>9.3  Cooperation with Loss Investigation. </u></strong> You agree to fully cooperate in any investigation that Wyth may choose to conduct if there is an incident (including a motor vehicle accident) in connection with a Carpool Trip. You will immediately send each request, demand, order, notice, summons or other pleading you receive in connection with any such incident to Wyth. You will not assume any obligation, make or commit to make any payment or incur any expense on Wyth’s behalf without Wyth’s prior written consent. </li>
            <li><strong><u>9.4  Survival. </u></strong> This Section 9 will survive termination of this Agreement.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
